Currently, JIRA will actually verify the status of assignee before allowing to close that issue. For example, if the user has been deleted or no long exist anymore in the directory, the JIRA administrator cannot close that issue simply because JIRA actually check and validate if the assignee is still belong to the directory. As an alternative we will need to reassign it to other users first before we can actually close the issue however this is quite tedious and troublesome if there are multiple users involved.

h3. From a customer perspective:
{panel}
The improvement is:
IMHO, Jira could allow me (as an Administrator) to close an issue regardless of the current status of the assignee. The action I attempted was to only close the issue. I did not want Jira to (re)verify the status of the assignee, and then block the close action if the user is not found.
{panel}

